<article id="post-179" class="post-179 post type-post status-publish format-image has-post-thumbnail hentry category-archive tag-imperialism tag-kipling post_format-post-format-image">
	
	<div class="post-thumbnail">
	<img width="1024" height="576" src="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/wp-content/uploads/White-Mans-Burden-1024x576.jpg" class="attachment-twentyfourteen-full-width size-twentyfourteen-full-width wp-post-image" alt="" />	</div>

	
	<header class="entry-header">
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="cat-links"><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/category/archive/" rel="category tag">Archive</a></span>
		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		<h1 class="entry-title">&#8220;The White Man&#8217;s Burden (Apologies to Rudyard Kipling),&#8221; cartoon, 1899</h1>
		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="post-format">
				<a class="entry-format" href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/type/image/">Image</a>
			</span>

			<span class="entry-date"><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/archive/the-white-mans-burden-apologies-to-rudyard-kipling-cartoon-1899/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-07-29T17:38:48+00:00">July 29, 2014</time></a></span> <span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/author/mp233/" rel="author">Mark Tseng Putterman</a></span></span>
						<span class="comments-link"><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/archive/the-white-mans-burden-apologies-to-rudyard-kipling-cartoon-1899/#respond">Leave a comment</a></span>
			
					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/wp-content/uploads/White-Mans-Burden.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-182" src="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/wp-content/uploads/White-Mans-Burden.jpg" alt="White Man's Burden" width="1024" height="671" srcset="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/wp-content/uploads/White-Mans-Burden.jpg 1024w, http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/wp-content/uploads/White-Mans-Burden-300x196.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>At the turn of the 20th century, as the United States flexed its imperial muscle in Hawai&#8217;i, Puerto Rico, and the Philippines, popular opinion increasingly linked imperial aspirations with a moral obligation to spread Western civilization and values to uncivilized peoples.</p>
<p>This Victor Gillam political cartoon from <em>Judge</em>, a New York-based satirical weekly, caricatures what the &#8220;civilizing mission&#8221; of Western imperialism promised. Following Great Britain&#8217;s John Bull, Uncle Sam is valiantly rescuing oppressed and barbarized peoples clambering up the rocks of ignorance and superstition toward &#8220;Civilization,&#8221; defined by &#8220;education&#8221; and &#8220;liberty.&#8221; However, this vision also evoked criticism and laid the foundations of fear. Was benevolent assimilation possible? What about the &#8220;troubles which may follow an imperial policy&#8221;?</p>
<p><em>Victor Gillam, &#8220;The White Man&#8217;s Burden (Apologies to Rudyard Kipling),&#8221; Judge, vol. 36, no. 911 (April 1, 1899). The Ohio State University Billy Ireland Cartoon Library &amp; Museum. </em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-meta"><span class="tag-links"><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/topic/imperialism/" rel="tag">Imperialism</a><a href="http://www.yellowperilarchive.org/topic/kipling/" rel="tag">Kipling</a></span></footer></article><!-- #post-## -->
